    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a pretty bleak outlook. but wouldn't proponents argue that those lower rates actually encourage investment and job creation, which could eventually help everyone through a \"trickle down\" effect? i'm seeing a lot of conflicting papers on whether that actually works or if it's just a myth.",
